{# 0500_ne_narrative_state.prompt — Director narrative-state injection.

   SkyrimNet auto-discovers every `.prompt` file under
   `prompts/submodules/system_head/` and injects it into the head of every
   assembled LLM prompt, regardless of which NPC is being rendered for.
   The numeric prefix (0500) controls our ordering relative to other
   `system_head` submodules.

   Reads two custom decorators registered at startup by NarrativeEngine's
   SKSE plugin (see Decorators.cpp). Both are global — the Director's
   narrative state is a property of the world, not a per-NPC fact — and
   our C++ side ignores the actor argument. BUT: SkyrimNet's
   `PublicRegisterDecorator` binds custom decorators as `(uuid) → string`
   functions, so the template MUST pass an actor UUID for the call to
   match. (We tried zero-arg calls; they silently returned empty, which
   in turn made `tnum` default to 0 and `phase` default to "" — both of
   which fall into the most-relaxed branches below.) We pass `npc.UUID`
   for whichever NPC SkyrimNet is rendering for; the value gets
   discarded on our side.

   Defensive `exists` check on `npc` so we don't error in render
   contexts where no NPC is in scope (we'd rather render nothing than
   render with default values, which would otherwise gaslight the LLM
   into thinking the world is always calm). #}
{% if exists("npc") and existsIn(npc, "UUID") %}
{% set tnum  = ne_narrative_tension(npc.UUID) | int %}
{% set phase = ne_narrative_phase(npc.UUID) %}
{% if   tnum < 20 %}{% set mood = "calm and unhurried" %}
{% elif tnum < 45 %}{% set mood = "watchful, with a faint undercurrent of unease" %}
{% elif tnum < 70 %}{% set mood = "noticeably tense — small troubles feel close at hand" %}
{% elif tnum < 90 %}{% set mood = "charged, as though the next hour might change everything" %}
{% else            %}{% set mood = "hot enough that the air itself seems to crackle" %}
{% endif %}
{% if   phase == "Exposition"    %}{% set arc = "the story is still settling in" %}
{% elif phase == "RisingAction"  %}{% set arc = "events are clearly building toward something" %}
{% elif phase == "Climax"        %}{% set arc = "matters are coming to a head" %}
{% elif phase == "FallingAction" %}{% set arc = "the worst seems to have passed, but its echoes linger" %}
{% else                          %}{% set arc = "things have settled into a new normal, for now" %}
{% endif %}

## Scene mood

The current mood of this scene feels {{ mood }}. Narratively, {{ arc }}. All actors present
should behave accordingly.
{% endif %}
